# Docker Engineering Standards

## Dockerfile Best Practices

### Multi-stage builds (mandatory for all services)
```dockerfile
# Stage 1: Build — fat image with all tools
FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder
# ... build steps

# Stage 2: Runtime — minimal image
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine AS runtime
# ONLY copy the built artifact
COPY --from=builder /app/target/*.jar /app/app.jar
```

### Security
- NEVER run as root: always add `USER 1000:1000` before `CMD`
- NEVER use `latest` tag for base images — pin to specific version (e.g., `17-jre-alpine`)
- NEVER put secrets in `ENV` or `ARG` — inject at runtime via docker-compose env
- Use `.dockerignore` to exclude: `node_modules/`, `target/`, `.env`, `.git/`

### Layer Caching (performance)
- Copy dependency manifests BEFORE source code to maximize cache hits:
```dockerfile
# Backend
COPY pom.xml .
RUN mvn dependency:go-offline -q   # ← cached if pom.xml unchanged
COPY src/ src/
RUN mvn package -DskipTests

# Frontend
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci                          # ← cached if package-lock.json unchanged
COPY . .
RUN npm run build
```

### Health Checks (required on all services)
```yaml
healthcheck:
  test: ["CMD-SHELL", "wget -qO- http://localhost:8080/actuator/health || exit 1"]
  interval: 15s
  timeout: 5s
  retries: 5
  start_period: 45s
```

## Docker Compose Structure
- `docker-compose.yml` — production-safe, no dev overrides
- `docker-compose.override.yml` — auto-merged in dev: Adminer, debug ports, volume mounts
- Use named volumes for all persistent data (PostgreSQL)
- Use named bridge networks — never use `network_mode: host`
- All services define `depends_on.condition: service_healthy`

## Image Naming
- GHCR: `ghcr.io/{owner}/slashai-{service}:{tag}`
- Tags: `latest` (main), `develop` (staging), `{sha}` (traceability)

## Resource Limits (Production)
```yaml
deploy:
  resources:
    limits:
      memory: 512m
      cpus: '0.5'
    reservations:
      memory: 256m
```
